# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# dsa-solvebook scraper — local development credentials
#
# Copy this file to `.env` (which is gitignored) and fill in your values.
# In GitHub Actions these are stored as Repository Secrets (never in code).
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── How to get your LeetCode cookies ─────────────────────────────────────────
# 1. Open https://leetcode.com in your browser and log in.
# 2. Open DevTools  →  Application (Chrome) or Storage (Firefox)
# 3. Navigate to  Cookies → https://leetcode.com
# 4. Copy the VALUE (not the name) of each cookie below.

# The session token — a long alphanumeric string, usually 200+ characters.
LEETCODE_SESSION=paste_your_LEETCODE_SESSION_cookie_value_here

# The CSRF token — typically a 32-character hex string.
LEETCODE_CSRF=paste_your_csrftoken_cookie_value_here

# ── Your public LeetCode username ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# This is the username shown in your LeetCode profile URL:
# https://leetcode.com/u/<YOUR_USERNAME>/
LEETCODE_USERNAME=your_leetcode_username
